Blocks.Text: Other Staff: Purchasing, Clerical Assistance Etc.
Cooking for Kids Chef Consult Structure
Build Collaborative Relationships: Instructions for Entry Conference
School Site's Meals per Labor Hour
Due to COVID-19, the 2020-21 Cooking for Kids Chef Consultations will most likely need to be adjusted to best meet the
needs of the school district/site. We understand some districts are not allowing outside visitors or may allow visitors but
have to shut down mid-year. Due to these circumstances, some pieces of the chef assessment will not be applicable.
Prior to starting the chef assessment, please answer the following questions and determine the best course of action in
terms of assessments. Throughout the chef consultation, revisit this section of the assessment to provide updates in
terms of school learning environment and meal service.
Chef Action Steps: Collect and Complete
Complete the following questions prior to starting the pre-chef assessment.
Identify assessments and areas of the pre-chef assessment that are not applicable due to COVID.
Continually provide updates throughout the chef consultation in terms of school learning environment and meal
1. At the time of the pre-chef assessment, how does the school district plan to deliver classroom learning?
2. At the time of the pre-chef assessment, how does the school district plan to serve meals to students? Options
are separated by where the students will consume the meals. Select all that apply.
Meals served in the cafeteria with no modifications
Meals served in the cafeteria with modifications
At the time of the pre-chef assessment, how does the school district plan to handle outside visitors? Select all
Allowing outside visitors in with no precautions (i.e. masks, frequent sanitation, social distancing, etc.)
Allowing outside visitors in with precautions
Not allowing outside visitors but allowing Cooking for Kids chef inside
Only allowing outside visitors when students are not on campus
4. How will the pre-chef assessment be conducted?
Virtually (i.e. Zoom, phone call, Facetime, etc.)
How to Complete the Pre-Chef Assessment
Consulting chef and school nutrition administration/management should complete the pre-chef assessment from the
perspective of what they plan to do at the time of the assessment.
If the consulting chef is not allowed in the school to complete the pre-chef assessment, the following
observations/assessments can be excluded. If this is the case, please indicate "N/A" clearly on the assessment tool:
The Mise en Place scorecard and the Smarter Lunchrooms scorecard can be completed via conversation with the CND or
kitchen manager, if the assessment is done virtually. For items not applicable due to COVID, please indicate "N/A" next
For all other pieces of the pre-chef assessment not previously mentioned that are affected by COVID and how the school
site is serving meals, the consulting chef should indicate "N/A" and an explanation of why it's not applicable or what the
school might be doing in place of the item.
